included.summary:
My goal as a designer is to build bridges between people, places, and things where interaction is lacking and users get left behind. With a BFA in Service Design from SCAD and my experience as a UX designer at one of the largest tech companies in the world, I'm curious to explore the interconnection between the on and offline world, where virtual touch points can foster trust and augment real world relationships. 

I believe that connecting people to worlds they might otherwise feel disconnected from is incredibly important, and am wildly curious about the many ways improvement can be made. I like to wear many hats, but my heart is in making something meaningful come to life.

Research. Make. Reflect (get outside, drink coffee). Repeat.

included.description: Over the course of 10 weeks, our team worked with the Civil Rights museum in Savannah, Georgia. We analyzed the stakeholders, performed a SWOT analysis, and researched local demographics to re design the museum experience. We found that the museum would benefit from further involvement with the local community. This collaboration lead to three implementation plans: host community events within the museum, design more interactive tours for schools, and re design the layout of the museum to reflect the time period more clearly. The museum also received a new logo and website selection presented by other design teams. This partnership was incredibly insightful and beneficial not only to our team (consisting of four service design students) but also to each of us individually. My part in this design challenge included all the storyboarding and visual conceptualization, conducting contextual research, creating simple mock ups, and facilitating the mapping and blueprinting of the museum experience.
included.title: Ralph Gilbert Mark Civil Rights Museum Service Upgrade
